description: From earlier feldishe, equivalent to field +‎ -ish.

adjectives.description: fieldish (comparative more fieldish, superlative most fieldish)

entries.meaning: Of, belonging to, or characteristic of the field; belonging to the country; rural.
examples: My mothers maydes when they do Sowe and SpinneThey ſing a ſonge made of the fieldiſh mowſe [cf. Egerton Manuscript 2711 version: “they ſang ſometyme a ſong of the feld mowſe”]that for becauſe her lyvelode was but thynnewoulde nedes go ſe her Towniſhe ſiſters howſe
